DURBAN - A ten-year-old girl has been rescued from what has been described as a house of horrors in Verulam, north of Durban. It is alleged the girl’s step-father raped her repeatedly after imprisoning her since the age of five. It is believed a neighbour came to her rescue after hearing her being beaten on Monday night. Residents in the area apprehended the man after the child revealed what had been happening. On Monday afternoon, Reaction Unit SA security officials said they had caught the suspect. Reaction Unit SA security officials say they have caught the suspect again after a tip-off. They’re handing him over to police now. #ChildRape pic.twitter.com/MMVDGHiy0Y eNCA